    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-01-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-01-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="249" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d249">
                <head>No. 548.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Robeson</persName> to Rear-Admiral <persName type="to">Davis</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Navy
                                        Department</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-01-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 3,
                                1874</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I transmit herewith a precept addressed to
                            you, as president of a naval court of inquiry, ordered to convene at the
                            Navy Department on the 7th instant, for the purpose of inquiring into
                            the causes of the foundering of the steam ship Virginius, recently
                            delivered to the United States by order of the government of Spain.</p>
                <p>Respectfully, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GEO. M. ROBESON,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of the
                                    Navy.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Rear-Admiral <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles H. Davis</hi>, U. S.
                                    N.,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington, D. C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
